<title>FRANCE: Valeo 1996 sales 28.87 bln Ffr.</title>
<headline>Valeo 1996 sales 28.87 bln Ffr.</headline>
<dateline>PARIS 1997-01-09</dateline>
<text>
<p>Year to Dec 31, 1996.</p>
<p>(All figures in millions of French francs)</p>
<p>Turnover				    28,870, up 14.4 percent.</p>
<p>NOTE - French car parts maker Valeo gave its sales figures in a statement. It said international sales rose 23 percent, representing 68 percent of group turnover versus 63 percent in the previous year. Sales in all its major markets rose strongly. Sales for Europe, outside France, increased 25 percent, 23 percent for North America and 16 percent in Asia and South America. In France, sales increased slightly, excluding asset disposals, helped by the state-backed rebate scheme which ran the first nine months.</p>
<p>It said it was too early to be certain of the economic recovery in Europe and the trend of car markets in Europe and America. Valeo will remain vigilant while maintaining its broad strategy for the coming year, it said.</p>
<p>-- Paris Newsroom +33 1 4221 5452</p>
